Participants had a strong belief in TCM for the treatment of both non-cancer and cancer. Over 50% of them had sometimes or often used TCM for a non-cancer illness and 84% of them used TCM as adjuvant therapy for cancer. OLR results demonstrated that belief in TCM for non-cancer and perceived effectiveness of herbs for cancer were significant predictors for belief in TCM for cancer, while income, number of prescribed herb names recalled and the total score of perceived effectiveness of TCM for cancer significantly predicted the total number of TCM modalities used for cancer.
